 Eric. [https://archive.org/details/nixonoliverstone00ston ''Nixon: An Oliver Stone Film'']. New York: [[Hachette Books#Hyperion Books|Hyperion Books]]. {{ISBN|978-0786881574}}. 598 pages.\n* Riordan, James. [https://archive.org/details/stonecontroversi00rior ''Stone: The Controversies, Excesses, and Exploits of a Radical Filmmaker'']. New York: [[Hachette Books#Hyperion Books|Hyperion Books]], 1996. {{ISBN|978-0786860265}}. 618 pages.\n* Salewicz, Chris. [https://archive.org/details/oliverstone0000sale ''Oliver Stone: The Making of His Movies'']. New York: [[Thunder's Mouth Press]]. {{ISBN|978-1560251620}}. 143 pages.\n* Scott, Ian and Henry Thompson. [https://archive.org/details/cinemaofoliverst00kaga ''The Cinema of Oliver Stone: Art, Authorship and Activism'']. [[Manchester University Press]], 2016. {{ISBN|978-1526108715}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Film|United States|Biography}}\n{{Commons}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* [http://www.oliverstone.com The Oliver Stone Experience (official Oliver Stone website)]\n* {{Britannica|567217}}\n* {{IMDb name|231}}\n* [http://www.filmmakers.com/artists/oliverstone/biography/ A biography of Oliver Stone]\n* [http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/MRC/stone.html Oliver Stone Bibliography (via UC Berkeley)]\n* [http://www.denofgeek.us/movies/oliver-stone/147030/oliver-stone-an-independent-american-director Oliver Stone, an Independent American Director]\n* {{C-SPAN|Oliver Stone}}\n* [http://www.wikitimelines.org/topics/oliver-stone Oliver Stone \u2013 a Timeline]\n\n{{Oliver Stone}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Oliver Stone\n|list  =\n{{AcademyAwardBestDirector 1981-2000}}\n{{AcademyAwardBestAdaptedScreenplay 1961-1980}}\n{{BAFTA Award for Best Direction}}\n{{DirectorsGuildofAmericaAwardFeatureFilm 1980-1999}}\n{{Golden Globe Award for Best Director 1966-1990}}\n{{GoldenGlobeBestScreenplayMotionPicture 1981-2000}}\n{{Honorary Golden Bear}}\n{{IndependentAwardforBestDirector}}\n{{Independent Spirit Award for Best Screenplay}}\n{{Satellite A